# Refactor Payment Dialog to Side Panel

## Goal Description
Refactor the payment interaction in the repairs table to open as a side panel (Sheet) on the right side instead of a modal dialog. This provides a better user experience for viewing details alongside the table.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> I will be creating a new UI component `Sheet` in `src/components/ui/sheet.tsx` which mimics the standard shadcn/ui Sheet component using `@radix-ui/react-dialog`.

## Proposed Changes

### UI Components
#### [NEW] [sheet.tsx](file:///home/amine/coding/web/tek-mag/frontend/src/components/ui/sheet.tsx)
- Create a `Sheet` component using `@radix-ui/react-dialog`.
- Implement variants for side positioning (right, left, top, bottom), defaulting to right.

### Features
#### [NEW] [payment-sheet.tsx](file:///home/amine/coding/web/tek-mag/frontend/src/components/features/commands/payment-sheet.tsx)
- Create a new component `PaymentSheet` based on [PaymentDialog](file:///home/amine/coding/web/tek-mag/frontend/src/components/features/commands/payment-dialog.tsx#27-204).
- Use `Sheet` instead of [Dialog](file:///home/amine/coding/web/tek-mag/frontend/src/components/features/commands/payment-dialog.tsx#27-204).
- Adjust layout for vertical space (side panel).

#### [DELETE] [payment-dialog.tsx](file:///home/amine/coding/web/tek-mag/frontend/src/components/features/commands/payment-dialog.tsx)
- Remove the old dialog component.

#### [MODIFY] [repairs-table.tsx](file:///home/amine/coding/web/tek-mag/frontend/src/components/features/calendrier/repairs-table.tsx)
- Import `PaymentSheet` instead of [PaymentDialog](file:///home/amine/coding/web/tek-mag/frontend/src/components/features/commands/payment-dialog.tsx#27-204).
- Update the state and render logic to use the sheet.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run `npm run build` to ensure no type errors or missing imports.
- (Optional) If there are existing tests for `repairs-table`, run them.

### Manual Verification
- Verify that clicking the payment action in the repairs table opens the sheet on the right.
- Verify that the sheet contains all the payment functionality (add, list, delete).
- Verify that the sheet closes correctly.
